cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CE 

This paper involves the application of machine learning algorithms on a medical dataset for classification purposes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of digitized images in the dataset suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The algorithms used in the paper are all related to artificial intelligence, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of hyper-parameters and manual assignment of them suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the focus on classification tasks suggests that it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
